### UI Permission Checks with PBAC (React)

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/packages/features/pbac/PBAC_REFACTORING_GUIDE.md

Demonstrates how to implement UI permission checks using PBAC in React components, shifting logic from client-side role checks to server-side permission verification. It involves fetching team IDs with specific permissions on the server and passing the resulting permission status as props to the UI components. This enhances security by ensuring permissions are validated before rendering UI elements.

```typescript
// Client-side role check with role-based variable name
const isTeamAdminOrOwner = user?.isTeamAdminOrOwner ?? false;
const canSeeMembers = isTeamAdminOrOwner;
```

```typescript
// Server-side permission check in page/layout
import { MembershipRole } from "@calcom/prisma/enums";

const permissionCheckService = new PermissionCheckService();
const teamIdsWithPermission = await permissionCheckService.getTeamIdsWithPermission({
  userId: session.user.id,
  permission: "team.listMembers",
  fallbackRoles: [MembershipRole.ADMIN, MembershipRole.OWNER],
});

const permissions = {
  canListMembers: teamIdsWithPermission.length > 0,
};

// Pass to component
<MyComponent permissions={permissions} />;
```

