### DataTableWrapper Props for UI and Layout in React

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/packages/features/data-table/GUIDE.md

Specifies the props for the 'DataTableWrapper' component, which handles the user interface and layout aspects of the data table, including pagination and toolbar configuration. This snippet details props like 'table', 'paginationMode', 'ToolbarLeft', 'ToolbarRight', and different loading state views.

```tsx
type DataTableWrapperProps<TData> = {
  table: ReactTableType<TData>;
  testId?: string;
  bodyTestId?: string;
  isPending?: boolean;
  totalRowCount?: number;
  variant?: "default" | "compact";
  className?: string;
  containerClassName?: string;
  headerClassName?: string;
  rowClassName?: string;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
  tableContainerRef?: React.RefObject<HTMLDivElement>;
  onRowMouseclick?: (row: Row<TData>) => void;

  // Toolbar slots
  ToolbarLeft?: React.ReactNode;
  ToolbarRight?: React.ReactNode;

  // Loading states
  EmptyView?: React.ReactNode;
  LoaderView?: React.ReactNode;
} & (
  // Infinite pagination
  | {
      paginationMode: "infinite";
      hasNextPage: boolean;
      fetchNextPage: () => void;
      isFetching: boolean;
    }
  // Standard pagination
  | {
      paginationMode: "standard";
      hasNextPage?: never;
      fetchNextPage?: never;
      isFetching?: never;
    }
);

```

