### DataTableProvider Context Values for State Management in React

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/packages/features/data-table/GUIDE.md

Outlines the context values exposed by the 'DataTableProvider'. This includes functions and states for managing filters, sorting, column visibility and sizing, pagination, segments, and search terms. This provides a comprehensive view of the state that can be accessed and manipulated within the data table component tree.

```tsx
type DataTableContextType = {
  // Filters
  activeFilters: ActiveFilters;
  addFilter: (columnId: string) => void;
  updateFilter: (columnId: string, value: FilterValue) => void;
  removeFilter: (columnId: string) => void;
  clearAll: (exclude?: string[]) => void;

  // Sorting
  sorting: SortingState;
  setSorting: OnChangeFn<SortingState>;

  // Column management
  columnVisibility: VisibilityState;
  setColumnVisibility: OnChangeFn<VisibilityState>;
  columnSizing: ColumnSizingState;
  setColumnSizing: OnChangeFn<ColumnSizingState>;

  // Pagination
  pageIndex: number;
  pageSize: number;
  setPageIndex: (pageIndex: number | null) => void;
  setPageSize: (pageSize: number | null) => void;
  offset: number;
  limit: number;

  // Segments
  segments: CombinedFilterSegment[];
  selectedSegment: CombinedFilterSegment | undefined;
  segmentId: SegmentIdentifier | null;
  setSegmentId: (id: SegmentIdentifier | null) => void;
  canSaveSegment: boolean;
  isSegmentEnabled: boolean;

  // Search
  searchTerm: string;
  setSearchTerm: (searchTerm: string | null) => void;
};

```
